The paper discusses the development of a framework for constructing and querying knowledge graphs, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and data integration. This suggests that the paper could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.DB (databases), cs.CL (computation and language), and cs.LG (machine learning). Among these, cs.AI and cs.IR seem to be the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the paper's focus on knowledge representation and question-answering. However, cs.DB and cs.CL are also relevant due to the paper's emphasis on data integration and natural language processing, respectively. Finally, cs.LG could be a possible category given the use of machine learning techniques in the framework.
